about Cadance's visit.

50
00:02:41,470 --> 00:02:43,320
What could you be
nervous about, Twilight?

51
00:02:43,780 --> 00:02:45,620
Cadance just loves
you to pieces!

52
00:02:45,990 --> 00:02:46,600
I know.

53
00:02:46,890 --> 00:02:49,010
But I really want her visit
to go without a hitch!

54
00:02:49,880 --> 00:02:50,990
Why wouldn't it?

55
00:02:51,500 --> 00:02:53,830
Well, the last few times
we've seen each other

56
00:02:54,010 --> 00:02:56,220
haven't exactly
been "worry free."

57
00:02:56,560 --> 00:02:58,840
The fate of Equestria
has hung in the balance

58
00:02:58,850 --> 00:03:00,410
during most of
your visits with her.

59
00:03:00,820 --> 00:03:01,560
Exactly.

60
00:03:01,810 --> 00:03:03,380
Cadance and I haven't
really had a chance

61
00:03:03,390 --> 00:03:05,140
to just enjoy being
friends again.

62
00:03:05,430 --> 00:03:07,650
Which is why it is so important
that this visit be about

63
00:03:07,660 --> 00:03:10,160
the two of us having some
real quality time together.

64
00:03:10,540 --> 00:03:12,870
I'm guessin' you've got a
plan that'll keep it that way.

65
00:03:13,220 --> 00:03:14,800
The timing couldn't
be more perfect.

66
00:03:15,110 --> 00:03:17,640
For one day only, right
here in Ponyville.

67
00:03:17,900 --> 00:03:20,590
The 'Starswirl the
Bearded' Traveling Museum!

68
00:03:20,760 --> 00:03:22,700
Cadance and I can spend
the whole day looking at

69
00:03:22,710 --> 00:03:24,080
Starswirl the Bearded artifacts.

70
00:03:24,490 --> 00:03:26,440
Sounds like the
perfect, drama-free way

71
00:03:26,450 --> 00:03:27,710
to spend the day
with Cadance.

72
00:03:27,860 --> 00:03:29,750
Not counting the drama
surrounding which of the bells

73
00:03:29,760 --> 00:03:31,770
from his cloak they've
chosen to put on display.

74
00:03:32,090 --> 00:03:34,620
Spoiler alert: It's this one.

75
00:03:35,190 --> 00:03:36,310
<i>(gagging)</i>

76
00:03:36,850 --> 00:03:38,380
Uh, heh heh, sorry.

77
00:03:38,540 --> 00:03:41,490
Something in my throat
like a big ball of "lame?"

78
00:03:42,140 --> 00:03:43,800
I think it sounds delightful.

79
00:03:44,170 --> 00:03:46,370
Yep. Definitely sounds
like you two will have

80
00:03:46,380 --> 00:03:48,360
some real quality
time together.

81
00:03:48,620 --> 00:03:49,390
Exactly.

82
00:03:49,600 --> 00:03:51,080
Just quiet time.

83
00:03:51,190 --> 00:03:53,290
<i>(train whistle)</i>

84
00:03:58,130 --> 00:04:03,110
<i>♪ (fanfare) </i>

85
00:04:08,010 --> 00:04:09,210
Your Highness.

86
00:04:10,440 --> 00:04:11,530
Your Highness.

87
00:04:12,960 --> 00:04:16,060
I'm teasing, Twilight.
We're sisters-in-law;

88
00:04:16,140 --> 00:04:17,590
we don't have to be so formal.

89
00:04:21,550 --> 00:04:23,130
<i>(train whistle)</i>

90
00:04:24,770 --> 00:04:27,180
Knowing you, you've
made some plans.

91
00:04:27,590 --> 00:04:30,580
Boy, have I. Hang on
just one second.

92
00:04:30,880 --> 00:04:31,550
You guys...

93
00:04:31,720 --> 00:04:34,260
Now, now, don't you
worry about a thing!

94
00:04:34,490 --> 00:04:37,060
We'll make sure that
nothing, but nothing,

95
00:04:37,070 --> 00:04:38,670
interferes with your visit.

96
00:04:38,980 --> 00:04:41,930
Go on! Have a hootenanny
with your kinfolk.

97
00:04:42,260 --> 00:04:45,090
You really are the best friends
a pony could ever have.

98
00:04:45,740 --> 00:04:47,220
Coming, Cadance!

99
00:04:49,010 --> 00:04:51,960
Ha! Two sisters-in-law bonding.

100
00:04:52,410 --> 00:04:53,920
Well, I for one am
gonna make sure

101
00:04:53,930 --> 00:04:55,350
that nothing spoils
their day.

102
00:04:55,360 --> 00:04:57,650
<i>(whistlin)</i>

103
00:04:57,660 --> 00:04:59,480
<i>Applejack: What is that thing?</i>

104
00:04:59,680 --> 00:05:01,580
Whatever it is...DUCK!

105
00:05:02,020 --> 00:05:04,130
Rarity, That doesn't look
anything like a duck!

106
00:05:05,370 --> 00:05:06,700
<i>(crash)</i>

107
00:05:07,770 --> 00:05:09,410
What is that?

108
00:05:10,770 --> 00:05:14,510
<i>Male voice: Not a what</i>
<i>but a "who," dear.</i>

109
00:05:14,860 --> 00:05:18,170
Oh, no, that sounds like...

110
00:05:18,180 --> 00:05:20,170
AAAAAAH-CHOOOO!

111
00:05:22,670 --> 00:05:23,780
DISCORD!

112
00:05:28,760 --> 00:05:30,780
What in tarnation
are you doin' here?

113
00:05:31,150 --> 00:05:33,420
And why the jumpin'
junebugs are you blue?

114
00:05:33,750 --> 00:05:36,030
More like a shade of
cerulean, to be precise.

115
00:05:36,310 --> 00:05:38,950
Whatever color you are
is the color of trouble!

116
00:05:39,410 --> 00:05:41,950
Oh, Rainbow Dash,
I've changed!

117
00:05:41,960 --> 00:05:45,030
Surely you remember
I was reformed

118
00:05:45,040 --> 00:05:50,040
by lovely little Fluttershy!

119
00:05:50,130 --> 00:05:51,130
<i>FLACHOOOOOO!</i>

120
00:05:51,140 --> 00:05:52,000
<i>(crash)</i>

121
00:05:52,310 --> 00:05:52,900
What are you?

122
00:05:53,040 --> 00:05:53,950
Sick or somethin'?

123
00:05:54,360 --> 00:05:56,440
Well, of course I'm sick!

124
00:05:56,740 --> 00:05:58,430
The blue skin?

125
00:05:58,840 --> 00:06:00,020
These sneezes?

126
00:06:00,410 --> 00:06:02,790
Could somebody find
me a fainting couch?

127
00:06:05,900 --> 00:06:06,440
What?

128
00:06:10,120 --> 00:06:12,230
Charming, thank you.

129
00:06:12,650 --> 00:06:14,870
I can't stop sneezing
and wheezing.

130
00:06:14,880 --> 00:06:17,930
In short, I need help.

131
00:06:18,980 --> 00:06:22,260
If you're so sick, why have
you come here instead of...

132
00:06:22,550 --> 00:06:26,150
y'know, staying home in bed and
getting over your weird illness?

133
00:06:26,870 --> 00:06:27,860
Achoo!

134
00:06:28,260 --> 00:06:30,120
<i>(honk)</i>

135
00:06:30,330 --> 00:06:33,060
Because this condition
has left me helpless.

136
00:06:33,300 --> 00:06:34,980
Simply helpless.

137
00:06:37,180 --> 00:06:39,840
Why, I can barely lift a spoon.

138
00:06:40,560 --> 00:06:42,030
<i>(crash)</i>

139
00:06:44,090 --> 00:06:47,320
I came to find the one pony
who truly understands me

140
00:06:47,330 --> 00:06:49,890
and could nurse me
back to health.

141
00:06:50,320 --> 00:06:52,770
Where is that dear,
sweet Fluttershy.

142
00:06:52,780 --> 00:06:54,080
I need attention!

143
00:06:54,090 --> 00:06:55,740
I need some care!

144
00:06:55,750 --> 00:06:57,000
I need...

145
00:06:57,010 --> 00:06:58,470
You need to chill!

146
00:06:58,970 --> 00:07:00,100
Fluttershy's out.

147
00:07:00,440 --> 00:07:01,630
Oh, of course.

148
00:07:02,060 --> 00:07:03,560
Her trip to see the
Breezies.

149
00:07:03,570 --> 00:07:05,680
Ah yes, I had forgotten
that was today.

150
00:07:06,200 --> 00:07:08,300
How do you know
about her trip?

151
00:07:08,440 --> 00:07:11,190
She told me about
it in her last letter.

152
00:07:12,780 --> 00:07:14,620
You and Fluttershy write
each other letters?

153
00:07:14,960 --> 00:07:15,980
Of course we do.

154
00:07:16,270 --> 00:07:17,460
We're friends.

155
00:07:17,500 --> 00:07:18,130
<i>(poof)</i>

156
00:07:18,150 --> 00:07:21,190
It's just such a shame
that today of all days

157
00:07:21,530 --> 00:07:23,520
is when I really need her.

158
00:07:23,760 --> 00:07:25,570
Oh, well. I know
what to do.

159
00:07:25,890 --> 00:07:28,300
Good thinking, head on
home, put your feet up.

160
00:07:28,310 --> 00:07:29,670
I'm sure eventually
you'll have the strength

161
00:07:29,680 --> 00:07:31,490
to make yourself
soup or something.

162
00:07:32,430 --> 00:07:33,810
No, no, no.

163
00:07:33,820 --> 00:07:37,980
I mean while she's gone, you
ponies can take care of me.

164
00:07:37,990 --> 00:07:39,810
Isn't that what
friends are for?

165
00:07:40,100 --> 00:07:41,970
Taking care of
each other?

166
00:07:43,430 --> 00:07:45,570
Let the healing begin!

167
00:07:46,360 --> 00:07:46,870
Not it!

168
00:07:46,990 --> 00:07:47,810
<i>(zoom)</i>

169
00:07:48,380 --> 00:07:51,580
Well! That's some way to
treat a suffering friend.

170
00:07:51,950 --> 00:07:53,000
ACHOOOO!

171
00:07:54,220 --> 00:07:56,280
Don't you worry, Discord,
I'll give you cuddles

172
00:07:56,290 --> 00:07:58,320
and read stories and
tell you all about me!

173
00:07:58,700 --> 00:08:00,230
I was born on a Tuesday....

174
00:08:00,570 --> 00:08:02,450
You're so sweet to offer.

175
00:08:02,690 --> 00:08:04,790
But Rarity and Applejack
already volunteered

176
00:08:04,800 --> 00:08:07,080
to be my own personal
nursemaids!

177
00:08:07,870 --> 00:08:08,890
We did?

178
00:08:09,520 --> 00:08:12,580
I SO hope you don't
mind, Pinkie Pie.

179
00:08:13,390 --> 00:08:15,420
Well, as a matter of
fact, I most certainly...

180
00:08:16,450 --> 00:08:19,460
Hey! Who keeps throwing away
these perfectly good balloons?

181
00:08:20,770 --> 00:08:22,030
That joker's
up to somethin'.

182
00:08:22,300 --> 00:08:24,470
And whatever it is, we're
gonna keep it as far away

183
00:08:24,480 --> 00:08:26,640
from Twilight and Princess
Cadance as possible.

184
00:08:27,700 --> 00:08:28,900
<i>(beeps)</i>

185
00:08:29,620 --> 00:08:30,230
You're right.

186
00:08:30,470 --> 00:08:32,780
We promised we wouldn't let
anything ruin their visit.

187
00:08:33,150 --> 00:08:35,560
Although I do so wish that
"anything" had turned out

188
00:08:35,570 --> 00:08:36,740
to be something else.

189
00:08:37,400 --> 00:08:40,820
Did I hear you two talking about
Princess Cadance's visit

190
00:08:40,830 --> 00:08:42,990
with Princess Twilight?

191
00:08:43,670 --> 00:08:44,420
Maybe.

192
00:08:44,840 --> 00:08:46,980
Fluttershy had mentioned
that those two

193
00:08:46,990 --> 00:08:48,030
were getting together today.

194
00:08:48,950 --> 00:08:50,410
How wonderful for them both.

195
00:08:50,620 --> 00:08:53,320
It is so rare that those two
get to see one another.

196
00:08:53,640 --> 00:08:56,210
I don't know about you, but I
sometimes wonder how close

197
00:08:56,220 --> 00:08:57,340
they could actually be.

198
00:08:57,350 --> 00:09:00,710
<i>All those years apart</i>
<i>before being reunited?</i>

199
00:09:01,510 --> 00:09:02,940
They're plenty close.

200
00:09:03,140 --> 00:09:05,690
And if they're not, this rare
opportunity to focus

201
00:09:05,700 --> 00:09:08,130
on their friendship will
certainly bring them closer.

202
00:09:08,480 --> 00:09:09,330
Unless...

203
00:09:09,340 --> 00:09:10,370
Don't even
think about it.

204
00:09:10,540 --> 00:09:11,930
They mustn't be disturbed.

205
00:09:12,030 --> 00:09:13,280
Disturb them?

206
00:09:13,490 --> 00:09:14,500
Why I wouldn't dream of it.

207
00:09:14,660 --> 00:09:17,040
Not when I have two such
dear friends of my own

208
00:09:17,150 --> 00:09:18,980
who have already offered
to take care of me.

209
00:09:19,270 --> 00:09:20,690
And at such peril.

210
00:09:21,780 --> 00:09:23,550
This flu of mine is highly...

211
00:09:25,190 --> 00:09:26,420
AAAACHOO!

212
00:09:26,520 --> 00:09:27,720
Contagious.

213
00:09:30,390 --> 00:09:31,690
AAAAAHHHHHCHOOO!

214
00:09:31,800 --> 00:09:32,540
<i>(crash)</i>

215
00:09:32,930 --> 00:09:35,790
Oh no! I've gotten
you both sick.

216
00:09:36,300 --> 00:09:40,680
Whomever shall I turn to
now in my time of need?

217
00:09:40,810 --> 00:09:42,320
<i>(evil chuckle)</i>

218
00:09:44,780 --> 00:09:47,680
Twilight: A whole day to
celebrate Starswirl the Bearded.

219
00:09:48,030 --> 00:09:49,170
What could be better?

220
00:09:49,460 --> 00:09:51,400
Absolutely nothing!

221
00:09:53,180 --> 00:09:55,200
Is that the candlestick
he used to light the way

222
00:09:55,210 --> 00:09:57,180
when he was exploring the
caverns of Maretania?

223
00:09:57,480 --> 00:09:58,750
It sure is.

224
00:09:58,940 --> 00:10:01,560
Oh, I can't believe I'm getting
to see it in real life!

225
00:10:01,640 --> 00:10:02,620
<i>(rattle)</i>

226
00:10:02,640 --> 00:10:03,910
<i>(poof)</i>

227
00:10:04,290 --> 00:10:05,080
<i>(squeals)</i>

228
00:10:05,560 --> 00:10:06,570
ACHOO!

229
00:10:12,350 --> 00:10:14,730
Discord! What are
you doing here?

230
00:10:15,080 --> 00:10:20,680
Oh, dear, dear Princesses,
I'm sorry to say I'm sick.

231
00:10:21,050 --> 00:10:22,910
<i>(cough)</i>

232
00:10:23,510 --> 00:10:24,620
Blue Flu.

233
00:10:24,960 --> 00:10:26,160
Blue Flu?

234
00:10:26,620 --> 00:10:29,600
I fear I've already given it
to poor Applejack and Rarity.

235
00:10:33,260 --> 00:10:34,220
Achoo!

236
00:10:35,420 --> 00:10:36,530
Magic health bubble.

237
00:10:37,000 --> 00:10:37,970
Good thinking.

238
00:10:38,360 --> 00:10:39,170
Indeed.

239
00:10:39,420 --> 00:10:40,990
How would Twilight
nurse me back to health

240
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:42,560
if she was sick, too?

241
00:10:43,080 --> 00:10:44,620
You will be letting
me stay at your place

242
00:10:44,630 --> 00:10:46,290
until I'm all
better, won't you?

243
00:10:46,840 --> 00:10:47,770
Stay?

244
00:10:48,030 --> 00:10:48,950
With me?

245
00:10:49,420 --> 00:10:51,590
Uh, now is not
really the best time.

246
00:10:51,890 --> 00:10:53,490
Though I'm sure you
already knew that.

247
00:10:54,130 --> 00:10:56,330
But taking in the sick
and the desperate:

248
00:10:56,530 --> 00:10:58,280
isn't that what
Fluttershy would do?

249
00:10:58,690 --> 00:11:02,270
Isn't "helping" something
that friends do for friends?

250
00:11:04,310 --> 00:11:05,220
Unless, of course,

251
00:11:05,610 --> 00:11:08,060
you're really saying that
you're not my friend.

252
00:11:10,800 --> 00:11:12,500
No. That is not
what I'm saying.

253
00:11:13,040 --> 00:11:15,200
Oh, how elated I
am to hear that.

254
00:11:16,560 --> 00:11:18,680
Shall the three of us
head back to your place?

255
00:11:19,040 --> 00:11:21,380
I don't want to get
anypony else sick.

256
00:11:21,410 --> 00:11:23,650
(sigh)I guess we
don't have much choice.

257
00:11:25,300 --> 00:11:26,330
Carry me?

258
00:11:26,620 --> 00:11:27,480
